&lt;p&gt;The South CAMHS Getting More Help service are looking for a new Child Wellbeing Practitioner to join our well established and highly regarded team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a CWP that would like to join the team, to offer Mental Health support to the south CAMHS locality. The successful candidate will offer low intensity interventions particularly focusing on Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT) and evidence based interventions. These interventions will be delivered through face to face appointments, IT applications such as Microsoft Teams, group work and consultation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main office is based at the Clockhouse in Abingdon on Thames. Abingdon is a market town conveniently situated 3 miles from Didcot with its train links, 2 miles from the A34 and 5 miles from the historic city of Oxford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namekelly GarsideJob titleClinical Team ManagerEmail addresskelly.garside@oxfordhealth.nhs.ukTelephone number01865-904700Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this post or arrange for an informal visit, then please contact Kelly Garside or Amanda Winfield on 01865-904700.&lt;/p&gt;
